ECLOGA X, BEMBUS.

Nunc verae et salsae discrimina relligionis Narrat, ovesque pias Carmeli separat hoedis.

The tenth Eclogue is a debate between the two great divisions of Mantuan’s order, the ObservanteS, or Discalced carmelites, and the Conventuals‚ who followed a mitigated rule. The speakers discuss the abuses which had crept into the order and caused the separation, and the umpire advises a return to the good old ways.
